def: To rend apart. [Obs.] Sir T. Browne.
Of or pertaining to a trochoid; having the properties of atrochoid.
Act of disclosing or uncovering something concealed. [Obs.]Boyle.
Relating to oleic acid, or elaine. Elaidic acid (Chem.), afatty acid isomeric with oleic acid, and obtained from it by theaction of nitrous acid.
Consisting of, or bearing, tubers; resembling a tuber.-- Tu"ber*ous*ness, n.
The quality or state of being welcome; gratefulness;agreeableness; kind reception.
The science of inscriptions; the art of engraving inscriptionsor of deciphering them.
A foundation or sustaining wall of stones thrown togetherwithout order, as in deep water or on a soft bottom.
Not conspicuous or noticeable; hardly discernible.-- In`con*spic"u*ous*ly, adv.-- In`con*spic"u*ous*ness, n. Boyle.
